name: Orange Wreck
description: Orange Wreck is the original homegrown cross of Trainwreck and a special (if not mysterious) old school Allagash strain. Exhibiting notes of pungent pine, fermented oranges, and funk, Orange Wreck offers consumers a challenging palate atop stimulating effects. This strain settles behind the eyes and in the body, igniting appetite and offering moderate pain relief.

highlightedReviews.text: A descendent of the Cali classic Train Wreck, Orange Wreck is a nice sativa dominant strain with a hodge-podge of pine, funk, and fermented orange scents. I've found that this strain works well when mixed with a chill OG strain, such as SFV OG, Larry OG or Ill OG. As a stand alone, Orange Wreck is great MEDICINE for reducing anxiety, fighting fatigue and depression, and providing cerebral stimulation that increases concentration and raises spirits. The flower is very aesthetically pleasing with tricomes galore. I've only sampled high-grade iterations of this strain, so to some degree, I am biased. But, as with most purchases, you receive what you pay for. So, spend the extra dough and partake in only quality expressions of Orange Wreck. ~As always peace and positive vibes & if you've found this review informative, keep the good vibes going by giving it a üëçüèΩ and follow me for more excellent reviews. Not a very energizing strain. Very middle of the road. Euphoria is short. Then nothing to write home about. It could be good for those looking for a mild sativa with pain relief. Good for a midday break though.
